def: A way out; exit. [R.]In divers streets and outways multiplied. P. Fletcher.
The quality or state of being uniform; uniformity.
Like, or coming near to, white. [Obs.]
The quality or condition of being bunchy; knobbiness.
An arrant coward; a dastard; a craven; a mean-spirited wretch.Shak.
A light yellowish green color resembling that of the pistachionut.
A bird having lobate toes; esp., a phalarope.
Strangely. [Obs.]Most strange, but yet most truly, will I speak. Shak.
